Default values are set inline using the class field initializer syntax. These defaults are used when the component first renders. Providing meaningful defaults avoids empty or broken initial UI states.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';

export default class PlayerDetailComponent extends Component {
  @tracked selectedPlayer = null;

