    {{/if}}
  </template>
}
```
The setter intercepts the assignment, validates the value, and either rejects it (with an error message) or commits it to the backing `@tracked` field. This centralizes validation logic and keeps `@action` methods clean. The `validationError` is itself `@tracked` so it renders reactively.

