```
Glimmer treats `null` and `undefined` as perfectly valid `@tracked` values. The autotracking system tracks the tag regardless of the value stored — transitioning from `null` to an object, or from an object back to `null`, both invalidate the tag and schedule a re-render. The developer is responsible for null-safe access inside getters using optional chaining (`?.`) and nullish coalescing (`??`). There is no special framework behavior for nullish tracked values; standard JavaScript defensive programming applies.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

export default class MatchDetailsComponent extends Component {
  @tracked match = { venue: 'MCG', format: 'Test' };

  @action
