In FastBoot (Ember's SSR environment), Glimmer renders components synchronously to a string. `@tracked` properties are initialized normally, getters are evaluated, and the template is serialized. However, there is no event loop, no user interactions, and no re-renders — the component renders once and is done. This means `@action` methods and any `@tracked` mutations triggered by user events never run during SSR. The initial values of `@tracked` properties (often derived from route model data via `@args`) determine the server-rendered HTML. Hydration in the browser then takes over and enables reactivity.

```gjs
