Glimmer schedules DOM updates asynchronously after tag invalidation. Setting a `@tracked` property marks the tag as dirty and queues a render microtask, but the DOM update has not yet happened when the next line of synchronous test code runs. `settled()` from `@ember/test-helpers` returns a Promise that resolves only after all pending renders, route transitions, and async tasks complete. Always `await settled()` after directly mutating `@tracked` state in tests that are not going through standard test helper actions like `click()` or `fillIn()`.

