Provide a `reset()` `@action` when the user needs to clear state while the component is still active (e.g., a "Clear" button on a form). Use `willDestroy` exclusively for cleaning up side effects that outlive the component (intervals, event listeners, WebSocket subscriptions). Setting `@tracked` properties inside `willDestroy` throws a development assertion error because Glimmer has already begun tearing down the component and no re-render will occur. The `@tracked` state is garbage collected with the component instance — no manual reset in `willDestroy` is needed or safe.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { TrackedSet } from 'tracked-built-ins';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

// Option A — @tracked array (simple but O(n) for lookups)
class OptionAComponent extends Component {
  @tracked selectedIds = [];
  @action toggle(id) {
    this.selectedIds = this.selectedIds.includes(id)
      ? this.selectedIds.filter(i => i !== id)
      : [...this.selectedIds, id];
  }
}

// Option B — TrackedSet (✅ Recommended for selection state)
export default class PlayerSelectorComponent extends Component {
  selectedIds = new TrackedSet();

  @action
  togglePlayer(id) {
    if (this.selectedIds.has(id)) {
      this.selectedIds.delete(id);
    } else {
      this.selectedIds.add(id);
    }
  }

  get selectedCount() { return this.selectedIds.size; }

  <template>
    {{#each @players as |player|}}
      <button
        class={{if (this.selectedIds.has player.id) "bg-blue-600" "bg-gray-200"}}
        {{on "click" (fn this.togglePlayer player.id)}}
      >{{player.name}}</button>
    {{/each}}
    <p>{{this.selectedCount}} selected</p>
  </template>
}
```
Use `TrackedSet` from `tracked-built-ins` for multi-selection state. Sets provide O(1) `has`, `add`, and `delete` operations, while array `includes` and `filter` are O(n). `TrackedSet` wraps each operation with reactive tracking, so the template re-renders when the set changes. Use a `@tracked` array when you need ordered selection, need to iterate with index, or cannot add the `tracked-built-ins` dependency.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
