    {{/if}}
  </template>
}
```
Store the full `Error` object in `@tracked error` for async operations. This preserves the stack trace for debugging, allows you to inspect `error.code`, `error.status`, or custom properties for conditional UI (show retry button only for network errors, not for validation errors). Use an error string only for simple validation messages that you construct yourself. Initialize `@tracked error = null` (not empty string) so `hasError` is a straightforward null check rather than string length comparison.

