If the component owns the state it is modifying, keep the `@action` local — it is self-contained and reusable. If the component is a presentational element (a button, a list item) and the data lives in the parent, accept the handler via `@args` and pass it directly to `{{on}}`. Avoid the anti-pattern of a child component that both displays parent data and also defines its own `@action` to modify state it doesn't own. Follow data-down-actions-up: data flows in via `@args`, user interactions flow out via `@args` callbacks.

```gjs
