Use ember-concurrency looping tasks for polling. The task is automatically cancelled when the component is destroyed, eliminating the `setInterval` + `willDestroy` cleanup pattern. The `while (true)` loop with `await timeout(30000)` is readable and testable — in tests, use fake timers or `timeout`'s test helpers. `task.isRunning` provides reactive live indicator for free. `setInterval` polling continues past component destruction without careful cleanup, causing memory leaks and errors.

