`@action` is designed for regular methods that handle events or mutations — it binds `this` and is intended for use with `{{on}}`. Applying it to a getter is semantically incorrect and may produce unexpected behaviour or warnings. Getters are already reactive when they read `@tracked` properties; no additional decorator is required.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG
