`@tracked` is a field decorator and cannot be applied to accessor methods like getters. Glimmer automatically tracks which `@tracked` properties a getter reads, and recomputes the getter whenever any of those properties change. Adding `@tracked` to a getter is redundant at best and throws a decorator error at worst.

```gjs
