```

Storing a derived value as `@tracked` state requires you to manually keep it in sync with its source data every time those sources change — this is error-prone and duplicates the source of truth. A getter is a single-source-of-truth computation that Glimmer automatically recomputes whenever the `@tracked` dependencies it reads change.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG — stale args inside @action
