import Component from '@glimmer/component';

export default class ScoreDisplayComponent extends Component {
  get score() {
    return this.args.score; // always reflects current parent value
  }

  <template>
    <p>Score: {{this.score}}</p>
  </template>
}
```

The constructor runs only once when the component is first instantiated. Copying `this.args.score` into a `@tracked` property in the constructor takes a one-time snapshot — subsequent parent re-renders that change the argument will not propagate to the local copy. Access `this.args` directly in the template or through a getter so the value is always current.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG
