```

`@tracked` is an instance field decorator — it sets up per-instance reactive state by hooking into Glimmer's tracking system on the prototype. Static properties belong to the class itself, not to any instance, so the tracking mechanism cannot be applied to them. Keep static properties as plain class fields and use instance `@tracked` properties for reactive state.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG — getter reads unrelated @tracked, causing unnecessary recomputes
