Glimmer recomputes a getter whenever any `@tracked` property read during the last execution changes. If a getter reads unrelated tracked state (even indirectly), it will recompute unnecessarily on every unrelated state change. Keep getters focused on the minimum set of tracked dependencies they actually need.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG
