During `willDestroy`, Glimmer has already committed the final render for the component. Updating a `@tracked` property at this point violates Glimmer's rendering constraints and triggers an assertion. If you need to track cleanup state, use a plain (non-tracked) instance flag, or cancel timers and subscriptions without touching reactive state.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG — anti-pattern
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

export default class LiveUpdateComponent extends Component {
