A raw `setTimeout` callback has no awareness of the component lifecycle. If the component is destroyed before the timeout fires, the callback still executes and mutates `@tracked` state on a destroyed component, causing an assertion error. `ember-concurrency` tasks are automatically cancelled when the component is torn down, making async state updates safe.

```gjs
