Glimmer's reactivity is tracked through the rendering context. A plain function called outside the render cycle has no association with the component's reactive graph, so reading `@tracked` properties inside it won't register dependencies or trigger re-renders. Keep reactive computations inside class getters or directly in the template.

```gjs
