`Ember.set()` integrates with the classic KVO (key-value observing) system which is not used in Glimmer components. Glimmer's reactivity is powered by `@tracked` and direct property assignment. Using `Ember.set()` on a Glimmer component does not trigger Glimmer re-renders and should be avoided entirely in modern Ember.

```gjs
