An `async @action` that `await`s a network call may complete after the component has been removed from the DOM. Updating `@tracked` state on a destroyed component throws an Ember assertion. `ember-concurrency` tasks are linked to the component's lifecycle and are automatically cancelled when the component is destroyed, preventing this problem entirely.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG — expensive getter re-runs on every render
