By default, Glimmer getters recompute every time the component renders, regardless of whether their tracked dependencies changed. For computationally expensive operations (large array reductions, complex filtering), use the `@cached` decorator from `@glimmer/tracking`. A `@cached` getter memoizes its result and only recomputes when its tracked dependencies actually change.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG — unnecessary chain
