`this.score++` does work with `@tracked` because it is equivalent to `this.score = this.score + 1` — it reads and then writes the property. However, it is less explicit and can confuse developers unfamiliar with how `@tracked` reactivity works. Prefer the explicit form `this.score = this.score + 1` for clarity, especially in team codebases.

