Initializing a boolean flag to `null` instead of `false` causes type inconsistency. While both are falsy in JavaScript, `null` is of type `object`, which can cause bugs in strict equality checks (`this.isLive === false` is false when `isLive` is `null`). Initialize boolean tracked properties to `true` or `false` to maintain type consistency throughout the component's lifecycle.

