Naming a `@tracked` property identically to an `@arg` creates confusion because `this.score` refers to the local tracked state, while `@score` (or `this.args.score`) refers to the parent-provided argument. A developer reading the code may expect them to be the same. Use a distinct name like `localScore`, `draftScore`, or `editableScore` for local tracked state that parallels an argument.

```gjs
