Loose equality (`==`) performs type coercion, so `'0' == 0` is `true`, `'' == 0` is `true`, and `null == 0` is `false` — all non-obvious. When comparing `@tracked` values use strict equality (`===`) and ensure the tracked property is initialised with the correct type. When reading values from `<input>` elements, always parse them with `Number()` or `parseInt()` before storing.

