`ember-concurrency` tasks come with built-in derived state: `.isRunning`, `.isIdle`, `.last.isError`, `.last.value`, and `.last.error`. Manually managing `@tracked isLoading` and `@tracked error` duplicates what the task already provides, adding unnecessary boilerplate and potential for synchronisation bugs. Use task-derived state directly in templates for cleaner, more reliable async patterns.

