Calling a parent callback with invalid data shifts the validation responsibility upstream, which breaks the single-responsibility principle and can corrupt application state. Validate tracked form fields inside the component before invoking any external callbacks. Use a `get isValid()` getter for reusable validation logic and a `@tracked validationError` property to surface errors in the template.

