User input often contains accidental leading or trailing spaces, particularly when pasting text. Comparing without trimming means `'  Rohit  '` does not match `'Rohit'`, producing empty results that appear to be a bug. Trim the query in the getter (rather than in the setter) to preserve the user's cursor position in the input while still comparing clean values.

