Glimmer owns the DOM it renders. Bypassing it with `document.getElementById(...).textContent = ...` puts the real DOM out of sync with Glimmer's internal representation. On the next render triggered by any other state change, Glimmer may overwrite your manual DOM changes, or leave the DOM in an inconsistent state. Always express UI updates as tracked state changes and let Glimmer reconcile the DOM.

