```gjs
// ✅ CORRECT — use ember-concurrency (auto-cancelled on destroy)
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { task } from 'ember-concurrency';

export default class SaveMatchComponent extends Component {
  @tracked isSaved = false;

  saveAndNavigate = task(async () => {
    await fetch('/api/match', { method: 'POST' });
    if (!this.isDestroying) {
      this.isSaved = true; // ember-concurrency also auto-cancels the task
    }
  });
}
```

If a route transition destroys the component while an async `@action` is in flight, the `await` resolves after destruction and the subsequent `@tracked` assignment throws an Ember assertion. `ember-concurrency` tasks are automatically cancelled when the component is destroyed, preventing post-destruction state mutations. As a secondary guard, check `this.isDestroying` before critical state updates in async operations.

