```

`Object.assign(target, source)` merges properties into the `target` object and returns the same `target` reference. When `target` is `this.match`, the tracked property's reference remains unchanged, so Glimmer detects no assignment and skips the re-render. Always use `Object.assign({}, this.match, changes)` (with an empty object as target) or object spread to produce a new reference.

