Glimmer components use a class-based model without support for the classic mixin pattern. `@tracked` decorators in a mixin function may not integrate correctly with Glimmer's prototype-based tag system and can produce unreliable reactivity. Share reusable reactive state and behaviour across components using Ember Services, which are proper dependency-injected singletons with full `@tracked` support.
